Gumtree Founders Sell Slando Website to Naspers, Times Says

-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 
2011-10-02T12:43:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/gumtree-founders-sell-slando-website-to-naspers-times-says.html
The founders of Gumtree, an on-line
advertising site owned by  EBay Inc. (EBAY) , have sold Slando, a
separate eastern European classifieds website, the  Sunday Times 
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Michael Pennington and Simon Crookall sold the site to
 Naspers Ltd. (NPN) , a South African media group, for an undisclosed
sum, according to the article.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Catherine Airlie in London at 
 cairlie@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  